<BES xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="BES.xsd">
	<Fixlet>
		<Title>Updated Red Hat Enterprise Linux Relay - IBM BigFix version 9.2.15 Now Available!</Title>
		<Description><![CDATA[
<DIV class=FixletMessage>
<TABLE><TBODY><TR><TD><P><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000><FONT color=#000000><STRONG>Version 9.2.15 of IBM BigFix is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux operating systems!<BR><BR></STRONG>The latest version of the IBM BigFix Relay provides several enhancements and fixes. This Fixlet can upgrade all Relays on the targeted computers.<BR><BR></FONT><STRONG><FONT color=red>You must upgrade your Relays to a 9.2 version before upgrading your Clients.</FONT><BR><BR><FONT color=#000000>Note:</FONT></STRONG></FONT><FONT color=#000000> This Fixlet message will only become relevant on computers after the IBM BigFix Server has been upgraded. Clients will notice that the IBM BigFix Server is updated and will begin to report any other upgrade Fixlets relevant (the clients by default check once per six hours for the version of the server on registration). This fixlet will also update the Client on any Relay installation.<BR><BR><STRONG>Note:</STRONG> It is recommended that you run this upgrade targeted to "All Computers" rather than to "Specific Computers" so that all old Relays and Clients will get upgraded.<BR><BR><STRONG>Note:</STRONG> This upgrade may take several minutes to run because the IBM BigFix Client will also be replaced as part of the upgrade process and the Clients will not report their action results right away.</FONT></FONT></P> <P><STRONG>Note:</STRONG> This relay runs on supported Red Hat Enterprise Linux platforms on 64-bit (versions 5, 6, 7) and 32-bit (versions 5, 6) processors.</P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV class=FixletProperty>
<H4>File Size:</H4>
41.0 MB
 </DIV>
]]></Description>
		<Relevance>(if exists property "in proxy agent context" then ( not in proxy agent context ) else true )</Relevance>
		<Relevance>not windows of operating system</Relevance>
		<Relevance><![CDATA[version of client >= "8.0"]]></Relevance>
		<Relevance>version of registration server = "9.2"</Relevance>
		<Relevance>evaluation of client license = false</Relevance>
		<Relevance>exists match (regex "Red Hat Enterprise (Client|Server|Workstation) (5|6|7)") of name of operating system</Relevance>
		<Relevance>((it = "x86_64") OR ((exists match (regex "^i[6-9]86$") of it) of it)) of architecture of operating system</Relevance>
		<Relevance><![CDATA[exists relay service whose (version of it < "9.2.15.15")]]></Relevance>
		<Relevance>if exists property "in agent context" then (in agent context) else true</Relevance>
		<Category>Upgrade</Category>
